---
to: "email-notification.html"
description: "Generate HTML email notification with responsive design"
category: notifications
requires:
  - subject
variables:
  subject: "Email subject line"
  from_email: "Sender email (default: noreply@example.com)"
  from_name: "Sender name (default: System Notifications)"
  to_email: "Recipient email"
  to_name: "Recipient name"
  template_type: "Email template type (alert, notification, report)"
  greeting: "Personalized greeting"
  body_text: "Email body text"
  cta_text: "Call-to-action button text"
  cta_url: "Call-to-action button URL"
  footer_text: "Footer text (default: unsubscribe info)"
  company_name: "Company name"
  company_logo_url: "Company logo URL"
  company_address: "Company address"
mode: overwrite



---






<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{{ subject }}</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .header {
      background: #f8f9fa;
      padding: 20px;
      text-align: center;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #dee2e6;
    }
    .logo {
      max-width: 200px;
      height: auto;
    }
    .content {
      padding: 30px 20px;
    }
    .greeting {
      font-size: 24px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      color: #2c3e50;
    }
    .body-text {
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .cta-button {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 12px 30px;
      background: #007bff;
      color: #ffffff;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .cta-button:hover {
      background: #0056b3;
    }
    .footer {
      background: #f8f9fa;
      padding: 20px;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #6c757d;
      border-top: 1px solid #dee2e6;
    }
    @media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {
      .container {
        padding: 10px;
      }
      .content {
        padding: 20px 10px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
{% if company_logo_url %}
      <img src="{{ company_logo_url }}" alt="{{ company_name }}" class="logo">
{% else %}
      <h1>{{ company_name | default("Company Name") }}</h1>
{% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <div class="greeting">
        {{ greeting | default("Hello " + to_name + ",") }}
      </div>

      <div class="body-text">
        {{ body_text | default("This is an automated notification message.") }}
      </div>

{% if cta_text and cta_url %}
      <div style="text-align: center;">
        <a href="{{ cta_url }}" class="cta-button">{{ cta_text }}</a>
      </div>
{% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
      <p>{{ footer_text | default("You received this email because you opted in for notifications.") }}</p>
      <p>&copy; {{ now | date("YYYY") }} {{ company_name | default("Company Name") }}</p>
{% if company_address %}
      <p>{{ company_address }}</p>
{% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>

## Signal Theory

**Signal**: `S=(linguistic, notification, inform, html, email-template)`
- **Mode**: linguistic
- **Genre**: notification
- **Type**: inform
- **Format**: html
- **Structure**: email-template

## Usage

```bash
# Generate email notification
unrdf template render \
  --template packages/cli/templates/notifications/email-notification.njk \
  --subject "Alert: Production Issue" \
  --to-email "user@example.com" \
  --to-name "John Doe" \
  --body-text "Service XYZ is experiencing downtime"

# Send email via sendmail
sendmail -t < email-notification.html

# Send via mailgun
curl -s --user 'api:{{ MAILGUN_API_KEY }}' \
  https://api.mailgun.net/v3/{{ MAILGUN_DOMAIN }}/messages \
  -F from='{{ from_email }}' \
  -F to='{{ to_email }}' \
  -F subject='{{ subject }}' \
  -F html=<email-notification.html
```

## Email Template Types

### Alert Email
```bash
--template-type "alert" \
--subject "🚨 Alert: {{ service_name }} Incident"
```

### Notification Email
```bash
--template-type "notification" \
--subject "📢 Update: {{ update_type }}"
```

### Report Email
```bash
--template-type "report" \
--subject "📊 Weekly Report: Week of {{ week_date }}"
```

## Best Practices

1. **Responsive Design**: Test on mobile devices
2. **Plain Text Fallback**: Always provide plain text version
3. **Unsubscribe Link**: Include opt-out mechanism
4. **SPF/DKIM**: Configure email authentication
5. **Test Before Sending**: Use email testing services

## Email Testing

```bash
# Use Mailtrap for testing
curl -s --user 'api:{{ MAILTRAP_API_KEY }}' \
  https://send.api.mailtrap.io/api/v1/send \
  -F from={{ from_email }} \
  -F to={{ to_email }} \
  -F subject="{{ subject }}" \
  -F html=<email-notification.html
```

